The House included immigration provisions in a bill for U.S. operations in Iraq and Afghanistan.
The REAL ID Act aims to prevent illegal immigrants from obtaining driver's licenses to enhance security.
Critics argue it will harm immigrant communities.
The bill, championed by Sensenbrenner, is seen as anti-immigrant and overly broad.
Lawmakers debate the impact on asylum seekers and the need for a national ID card.
Some fear it will hinder safe haven for immigrants.
The bill's implications on national security and immigration reform are hotly contested, with concerns over bureaucratic burdens and insurance issues for illegal immigrants.
